2 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
3 integral part of Title 39, chapter 71, and the provisions of Title 39, chapter 71, apply to [section 1].
4
5 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Severability. If a part of [this act] is invalid, all valid parts that are
6 severable from the invalid part remain in effect. If a part of [this act] is invalid in one or more of its applications,
7 the part remains in effect in all valid applications that are severable from the invalid applications.
8
9 NEW SECTION. Section 7. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 8. Applicability. [This act] applies to claims for workers' compensation in
12 which a diagnosis finds that the injury or occupational disease of posttraumatic stress disorder was caused by
13 events occurring on or after [the effective date of this act].
